# Cron job configuration for Daily Question Bank Pipeline
# Run daily at 6:00 AM IST (adjust as needed)

# Usage:
# 1. Make script executable: chmod +x scripts/setup_cron.sh
# 2. Run setup: ./scripts/setup_cron.sh
# 3. Or manually add to crontab:
#    crontab -e
#    Add: 0 6 * * * cd /path/to/project && /usr/bin/python3 scripts/run_daily_pipeline.py >> logs/cron.log 2>&1

# Example crontab entry:
# 0 6 * * * cd /Users/techmarbles/Documents/DailyQuestionBank-automation && /usr/bin/python3 scripts/run_daily_pipeline.py >> logs/cron.log 2>&1

# To view cron logs:
# tail -f logs/cron.log

# To remove cron job:
# crontab -e
# (Remove the line containing run_daily_pipeline.py)

